Alexander Ilyin (Russian: Алекса́ндр Влади́мирович Ильи́н, (born January 11, 1973) is a Russian mathematician, Professor, Dr. Sc., a professor at the Faculty of Computer Science at the Moscow State University, Corresponding Member of the Russian Academy of Sciences. Expert in robust control theory.
