Sergei Mukhin (Russian: Серге́й Ива́нович Му́хин) (born 1959) is a Russian mathematician, Professor, Dr.Sc., and a professor at the Faculty of Computer Science at the Moscow State University.
He graduated from the faculty MSU CMC in 1981. Mukhin has worked at Moscow State University since 1984. In 2009, he defended his thesis "Mathematical modeling of hemodynamics" for the degree of Doctor of Physical and Mathematical Sciences. He has authored 3 books and more than 80 scientific articles.

Summary: 
Sergei Mukhin, born on September 22, 1959, in Moscow, is a prominent Russian mathematician and professor. He graduated from Moscow State University in 1981 and has been working at the Faculty of Computer Science (MSU CMC) since 1984. Under the advisory of Yuri Popov, he defended his doctoral thesis, "Mathematical modeling of hemodynamics," in 2009. A Doctor of Physical and Mathematical Sciences, Mukhin's academic contributions include authoring three books and over 80 scientific articles. This provides a comprehensive overview of his life and career, successfully fulfilling the user's request.
