Mukhamet Kharrasov (1948–2024) was a distinguished Russian physicist and academician. He earned his degrees from Bashkir State University and Moscow State University, and subsequently served as the rector of Bashkir State University from 2000 to 2010. Kharrasov was recognized as a Doctor of Physical and Mathematical Sciences and an Honored Scientist of the Russian Federation. His primary research interests included the physics of superconductivity, stochastic diffusion processes in dissipative systems, and dynamic exchange interactions in condensed matter. Additionally, he served as a deputy in the State Assembly of Bashkortostan.
